title: This is absolutely perfect! - 5 stars for the product plus bonus points for customer service
text:
When I saw this piece of handmade jewelry, I knew it was the perfect gift for my son's newly engaged wife to be for her birthday. And I can't say enough about Kiara, the lady who makes it. I had questions about delivery because it was a late find, and she was extremely prompt with her replies and also went out of her way to make sure to ship it early so that I got it in time. Such a sweet lady, and I am additionally proud to help support a military family. I hope she sells a lot of these and is very successful.

Nearly 4 years ago, my son lost his young bride in a car accident, leaving him and their two kids without a wife and mother. Family has always been very important to us, but families huddle and take care of each other during those really rough times and we huddled a lot. Having to care for his family as well as support from his extended family and the family of his wife were the things that held him together.

Just a few weeks ago, he became engaged again, planning to marry this June. Oddly, both his late wife and new fiance are the eldest of 5 siblings in very strong families, and we knew the minute we met her that she would become one of ours. And though they didn't realize the significance of it till a day later, my son proposed to her at the Ohana Restaurant at Disney World. How fitting is that?!?

So when I saw this pendant, I knew it was the perfect gift for our future daughter in law. It's not expensive, but it is nicely made and simple elegance. Actually, the picture doesn't even come close to doing it justice, as it is so much nicer than expected. The seller puts the item in a small gift bag with a little bow on this, and I know our future daughter in law will be as tickled to receive it as I was to find it. Thanks Kiara for your prompt attention and assistance, and thank you to you and your husband for his service to our country.

Update: After wearing these for 9 months, they have held together beautifully. They are great for my sensitive ears still. The color still looks beautiful. I love these. I get compliments everywhere I go with these earrings.

The first thing I noticed was how accurate the color was when I first got these in the mail. I ordered this pair because I totally love the color of the picture. I wasn't sure if they were going to be more minty, or more turquoise like the picture. If I had to pick, I'd say just a little more turquoise than mint, but that's perfectly fine to me because it matched the picture, and they are STUNNING in person. Very, very nice color.

The earrings themselves are very impressive for 12 dollars. Buying handcrafted stuff can sometimes be hit or miss, but these are very much a hit. The wood contrasts perfectly with the turquoise, and these things are smooth as could be.

I'm allergic to nickel, and I was pleased to find that these are indeed nickel free. Says so in the packaging, and my tender ears confirmed that there is no nickel. Something else I REALLY appreciated was the fact that the earring backs are very strong. You can hear them click over the grooves, so I don't expect that they'll be slipping off anytime soon. My husband can appreciate this because he finds most of my earring backs on the floor after a few weeks. They are also very light, so they don't tug against my ears.

title: Beautiful!  Highly recommend this product.
text:
I've been a fan of the Dodge Ram for many, many years. When I learned that Custom Car Posters was making a ram generations poster I had to get it! I purchased the 24" x 36", with blue trucks, on satin paper. You can see in the picture that it came out great! The frame actually decreases the quality a bit, as the Target-brand frame I put it in is somewhat translucent rather than transparent. The poster is sharper out of this frame.

When I received the poster originally (I received it within a week, by the way -- don't be discouraged by the lead time quoted by Amazon) the box was unfortunately damaged in transit and the poster was badly crimped as a result. The crew at Custom Car Posters immediately made me another one and shipped it with improved shipping materials. They mentioned that USPS is generally very reliable, from a quality standpoint, in their experience.

My box came with a thank-you card as well as a sheet of fun car stickers! Too bad there weren't any Rams on the sticker, but, knowing this is a newer design for them it is not surprising that their existing stickers don't yet have the ram truck on them.

Overall, I'm very satisfied with the quality of the poster and the support experience I've had with CCP.
